Defendant Kenneth T Lewis in court with attorney Louis Edward Epps.  Defendant Kenneth T Lewis in custody.  Megan Marie Williamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess firearms and that he may not vote until his civil rights have been restored.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Kenya L. and Jacqueline W.  The Court imposed the following sentence:   

The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 20 years  consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 15 years.  Defendant shall serve 5 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for  the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * DNA sample ordered in 15CF395.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharge, plus costs and disbursements, from monies to be taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of defendant's prison funds.  Balance to be paid while on Extended Supervision.
 * Court ordered defendant to have no contact with any gangs or be involved in gang activity.
 * Court ordered defendant to have no contact with Marquis L., Takeyra J. or Tiora W. either directly or by third parties.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Continued no contact with Marquis L., Takeyra J. or Tiora W. personally or by third party contact;
 - No gang involvement or activity;
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation; follow any treatment recommended;
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician;
 - No alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Court ordered defendant to pay any balances remaining of the DNA surcharge, costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

At the request of defense counsel, Court reinstated phone privileges reminding defendant that there is a no contact order in effect.  Court ordered defendant remanded.

Filed,
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
